#compdef csv2arrow
# =============================================================================
# csv2arrow — domoritz/arrow-tools's CSV-to-
#   APACHE-ARROW-IPC converter — a focused
#   single-purpose Rust CLI that reads a CSV
#   (optionally gzipped, optionally with
#   user-supplied JSON schema) and writes the
#   data as an Apache Arrow IPC (a.k.a.
#   Feather / Arrow Streaming) binary file.
#   Built on direct `arrow 58.1` — the
#   CANONICAL pure-Rust Apache Arrow library
#   maintained by the Apache Software
#   Foundation under the `arrow-rs` umbrella.
#   Performs automatic SCHEMA INFERENCE by
#   sampling the first N rows, or accepts an
#   explicit `--schema-file` JSON spec.
#   Rust=109 leader bump opening Axis 54.
#
# AXIS 54 — APACHE ARROW COLUMNAR FORMAT — OPENS @ R805
# ======================================================
# Establishes the 54th three-language axis in
# the corpus.  This axis covers CLI tools
# written in language X that ship a DIRECT
# library binding to APACHE ARROW — the
# columnar in-memory data format + IPC
# protocol used by DataFusion, DuckDB,
# Polars, PySpark, Pandas (via PyArrow), and
# basically every modern analytical query
# engine.  Canonical implementations per
# language:
#   * Rust       : arrow (this entry)
#                  — apache/arrow-rs/arrow.
#                    ~3.2k stars (workspace
#                    aggregate).  The
#                    REFERENCE pure-Rust
#                    implementation of the
#                    Arrow columnar format +
#                    IPC + Flight RPC + CSV/
#                    JSON/Parquet reader-
#                    writer integrations.
#                    Apache 2.0
#                  — version 58.1 used here
#                  — direct dep at
#                    `domoritz/arrow-tools`
#                    crates/csv2arrow/
#                    Cargo.toml line:
#                    `arrow = "58.1"`
#   * Go         : apache/arrow-go — Apache's
#                  Go implementation
#                  (formerly nested inside
#                  apache/arrow; now a
#                  standalone module at
#                  apache/arrow-go/v18 since
#                  Arrow 18).  R806 will
#                  close the Go side
#   * TS-Node    : apache-arrow — Apache's
#                  JS/TS implementation,
#                  published as the
#                  `apache-arrow` npm
#                  package.  R807 will
#                  close the TS-Node side
#
# Apache Arrow standardises a LANGUAGE-
# INDEPENDENT COLUMNAR FORMAT for in-memory
# analytical data.  Buffers are
# canonicalised so that the same memory
# layout works across all 11 host languages
# (C++, Rust, Go, Java, Python, R, C#,
# JavaScript, Julia, MATLAB, Ruby).  Arrow
# Flight is an Arrow-native gRPC protocol
# for streaming Arrow record batches
# between systems.  Used as the wire format
# of:
#   - DuckDB → Pandas / Polars            zero-copy
#                                          interchange
#   - Apache Spark ↔ PyArrow              Pandas-on-Spark
#   - DataFusion (Rust) ↔ Polars (Rust)   zero-copy
#                                          batches
#   - dremio Arrow Flight protocol        OLAP
#                                          streaming
#   - BigQuery Storage API (BSA)          column-stream
#                                          read
#
# Distinguishing csv2arrow from sibling
# corpus tools:
#   - csv2parquet (`_csv2parquet`, in
#     corpus): SAME maintainer (Dominik
#     Moritz), SAME workspace; converts to
#     Parquet (on-disk columnar) instead
#     of Arrow IPC (in-memory streaming).
#     Both use the `arrow-rs` ecosystem
#   - json2arrow (`_json2arrow`, free —
#     not yet in corpus): SAME maintainer,
#     SAME workspace; reads JSON instead
#     of CSV
#   - json2parquet (`_json2parquet`, in
#     corpus): SAME maintainer; JSON → Parquet
#   - DuckDB `duckdb` (`_duckdb` in corpus):
#     can also do `COPY ... TO 'out.arrow'`,
#     but is a full SQL engine.  csv2arrow
#     is the focused single-purpose
#     converter
#   - q (sql-on-csv, in corpus): different
#     scope — SQL over CSV without
#     materialising Arrow
#   - mlr (`_mlr`, miller, in corpus): CSV/
#     TSV/JSON record-stream processor.
#     No Arrow output
#
# WHEN TO USE CSV2ARROW vs CSV2PARQUET:
#   - Use CSV2ARROW when downstream consumers
#     speak Arrow IPC (PyArrow / Polars /
#     DuckDB streaming read / Arrow Flight
#     server).  Arrow IPC is OPTIMISED FOR
#     IN-MEMORY STREAMING — no compression
#     by default, fast random access via
#     dictionary indexes, mmap-friendly
#   - Use CSV2PARQUET when downstream
#     consumers need ON-DISK COMPRESSED
#     STORAGE — Parquet adds page
#     compression (Snappy/Zstd/Brotli),
#     dictionary encoding per-column, row-
#     group statistics for predicate
#     pushdown, schema-evolution support
#
# KEY CSV2ARROW FEATURES:
#   - STREAMING WRITE — the binary uses
#     `arrow::ipc::writer::FileWriter` which
#     emits Arrow IPC frames as records
#     arrive.  Memory footprint is bounded
#     by the record batch size, not the
#     input file size.  Gigabyte-scale CSVs
#     convert without OOM
#   - SCHEMA INFERENCE — by default,
#     samples the first N rows
#     (configurable via `--max-read-records`)
#     to infer column types.  Setting
#     `--max-read-records 0` skips inference
#     and types every column as String
#   - EXPLICIT SCHEMA OVERRIDE — `-s/
#     --schema-file <PATH>` loads an Arrow
#     schema in JSON format (same JSON
#     dialect that `arrow-rs` uses for its
#     `Schema::from_json` deserialisation).
#     Skips inference entirely.  Critical
#     for reproducible CI pipelines where
#     type-stability matters
#   - CSV DIALECT CONTROL — `--delimiter`
#     (single char, default `,`),
#     `--escape`, `--quote`, `--comment`
#     all settable.  Matches Python's csv
#     module API
#   - NULL REGEX — `--null-regex <PATTERN>`
#     treats any field matching the regex
#     as NULL.  Common patterns:
#     `--null-regex '^(NA|NULL|N/A|-)$'`
#   - GZIP TRANSPARENT READ — input files
#     ending in `.gz` are decompressed in-
#     stream via `flate2/MultiGzDecoder`.
#     No manual `gunzip` step needed
#   - STDOUT FALLBACK — if no `<ARROW>`
#     output argument is given, writes
#     Arrow IPC bytes to stdout.  Pipeable
#     into PyArrow / Polars / DuckDB
#     streaming readers
#   - DRY-RUN — `-n/--dry` prints only the
#     INFERRED SCHEMA (to stderr) and
#     exits.  Useful for confirming type
#     inference before committing to a
#     conversion
#   - PRINT-SCHEMA — `-p/--print-schema`
#     prints the schema to stderr in
#     ADDITION to producing the Arrow
#     output.  Combine with `--dry` for
#     schema-only mode
#
# ARROW IPC vs FEATHER V2:
# `arrow::ipc::writer::FileWriter` emits the
# "File" variant of Arrow IPC (also marketed
# as "Feather v2").  The "Stream" variant is
# similar but lacks the trailing footer.
# This binary always produces the File
# variant — readable by `pyarrow.feather.
# read_feather()`, `polars.read_ipc()`,
# `duckdb.read_arrow()`, and arrow-rs's
# `arrow::ipc::reader::FileReader`
#
# CRITICAL DIRECT DEPENDENCIES (from
# crates/csv2arrow/Cargo.toml):
#   - arrow 58.1               — Apache Arrow
#                                Rust impl
#                                [AXIS 54 LIBRARY]
#                                provides
#                                CSV reader,
#                                IPC writer,
#                                schema
#                                types
#   - arrow-schema 58.1 (serde)
#                              — Arrow
#                                schema JSON
#                                deserialisation
#   - serde_json 1.0           — JSON parse
#                                for schema
#                                file
#   - clap 4.5 (derive)        — CLI parser
#   - regex 1.12               — null-regex
#                                pattern
#                                matching
#   - flate2 1.1 (zlib-ng)     — transparent
#                                gzip
#                                decompression
#                                for .gz
#                                input
#   - libz-ng-sys              — zlib-ng
#                                C bindings
#   - arrow-tools 0.26 (path)  — shared
#                                workspace
#                                utility
#                                crate
#                                (provides
#                                SeekableReader
#                                for stdin/
#                                non-seekable
#                                inputs)
#
# Rust 2021 edition.  Tested with stable
# Rust 1.85+.  Cross-platform: builds on
# Linux + macOS + Windows.  Single-file
# binary; no external runtime deps in the
# emitted executable
#
# UPSTREAM:
#   * Source             : https://github.com/domoritz/arrow-tools/tree/main/crates/csv2arrow
#   * Workspace          : https://github.com/domoritz/arrow-tools
#   * Apache Arrow Rust  : https://github.com/apache/arrow-rs
#   * Arrow IPC spec     : https://arrow.apache.org/docs/format/Columnar.html
#   * Feather v2 docs    : https://arrow.apache.org/docs/python/feather.html
#   * License            : MIT OR Apache-2.0
#   * Maintainer         : Dominik Moritz (domoritz)
#
# INSTALL:
#   # Cargo
#   cargo install csv2arrow
#
#   # Cargo + the whole arrow-tools workspace
#   git clone https://github.com/domoritz/arrow-tools
#   cd arrow-tools
#   cargo install --path crates/csv2arrow
#
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
#
#   # Convert a CSV to Arrow IPC (output file
#   # required as 2nd positional)
#   csv2arrow input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Write to stdout (no 2nd positional)
#   csv2arrow input.csv > output.arrow
#
#   # Sample only the first 1000 rows for
#   # schema inference
#   csv2arrow -m 1000 input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Force every column to String (skip
#   # inference)
#   csv2arrow -m 0 input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Use an explicit Arrow schema (JSON)
#   csv2arrow -s schema.json input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Headerless CSV
#   csv2arrow --header false input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Tab-separated values
#   csv2arrow --delimiter $'\t' input.tsv output.arrow
#
#   # Pipe-separated values with a quote char
#   csv2arrow --delimiter '|' --quote '"' \
#       input.psv output.arrow
#
#   # Treat "NA", "NULL", "N/A", "-" as nulls
#   csv2arrow --null-regex '^(NA|NULL|N/A|-)$' \
#       input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Ignore comment lines starting with #
#   csv2arrow --comment '#' input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Gzipped input (decompressed in-stream)
#   csv2arrow input.csv.gz output.arrow
#
#   # Print the inferred schema to stderr +
#   # produce output as usual
#   csv2arrow -p input.csv output.arrow
#
#   # Dry-run — print schema only, no Arrow
#   # output
#   csv2arrow -n input.csv
#
#   # Help / version (clap defaults)
#   csv2arrow --help
#   csv2arrow -h
#   csv2arrow --version
#   csv2arrow -V
#
# DOWNSTREAM CONSUMPTION:
#
#   # PyArrow / pandas
#   import pyarrow.feather as f
#   table = f.read_feather('output.arrow')
#
#   # Polars
#   import polars as pl
#   df = pl.read_ipc('output.arrow')
#
#   # DuckDB
#   SELECT * FROM 'output.arrow';
#
#   # arrow-rs (Rust)
#   let file = File::open("output.arrow")?;
#   let reader = arrow::ipc::reader::FileReader::try_new(file, None)?;
#
# OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/domoritz/arrow-tools/blob/main/crates/csv2arrow/src/main.rs Opts struct):
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

_arguments -C \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
    '(-s --schema-file)'{-s+,--schema-file=}'[file with Arrow schema in JSON format (skips inference)]:schema:_files -g "*.json"' \
    '(-m --max-read-records)'{-m+,--max-read-records=}'[records to sample for schema inference (0 = all-String)]:n: ' \
    '--header=[CSV has headers (default true)]:bool:(true false)' \
    '--delimiter=[CSV column delimiter (single char)]:char: ' \
    '--escape=[CSV escape character]:char: ' \
    '--quote=[CSV quote character]:char: ' \
    '--comment=[CSV comment character (lines starting with this are ignored)]:char: ' \
    '--null-regex=[regex matching NULL field values]:pattern: ' \
    '(-p --print-schema)'{-p,--print-schema}'[print inferred schema to stderr]' \
    '(-n --dry)'{-n,--dry}'[only print the schema (no Arrow output)]' \
    '1:input CSV file (or - for stdin):_files -g "*.(csv|tsv|csv.gz|tsv.gz)"' \
    '2:output Arrow IPC file (stdout if omitted):_files -g "*.(arrow|feather|ipc)"' \
    && ret=0

return ret
